======================================================================
ANALYSIS 7: Rank formulas
======================================================================
Rank relationships (from beta_2 = 0 and chi):
  rk(d_1) = n - 1 = 4
  rk(d_2) = C(n-1,2) - beta_1 = 6 - beta_1
  rk(d_3) = dim(Om_2) - C(n-1,2) + beta_1  [from beta_2=0]
  chi = 1 always => beta_1 + beta_3 = beta_4 + beta_5 + ...

  chi distribution at n=5: {0: 304, 1: 720}
  chi is NOT always 1

Done.
